894
00:43:21,580 --> 00:43:26,340
The red of the setting sun
tinges the pristine snow

895
00:43:26,700 --> 00:43:31,580
Swans return successively,
fulfilling the promise of spring

896
00:43:32,340 --> 00:43:36,540
From whence does the wind invite,
a few plum blossoms to float

897
00:43:37,660 --> 00:43:42,060
I entrust my longing,
waiting for you to know

898
00:43:43,020 --> 00:43:47,220
A single lamp flickers,
with curling smoke in the air

899
00:43:48,580 --> 00:43:52,940
Magpies perch on branches,
guarding our lifelong attachment

900
00:43:53,700 --> 00:44:00,460
No matter how far you go,
home will illuminate your night

901
00:44:04,140 --> 00:44:08,580
